Privacy Policy for Pinterest App
Last updated: October 24, 2025

1. Introduction

Welcome to Pinterest App (“we”, “our”, or “us”). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our Pinterest-connected app or service.

By using the app, you agree to the terms described below.

2. Information We Collect

We may collect the following information when you connect your Pinterest account:

Your Pinterest public profile information (name, username, profile picture)

Boards, pins, and related metadata (only when you grant permission)

Email address (if provided and authorized)

Technical and usage data (browser type, timestamps, IP address)

If you contact us directly, we may also store your message and contact details to respond.

3. How We Use Information

We use the collected information to:

Provide, operate, and improve the app

Authenticate your Pinterest account

Display and manage your Pinterest content

Respond to questions or feedback

Monitor and prevent misuse or unauthorized access

We do not sell, rent, or trade your information.

4. Data Sharing

We share data only in these limited cases:

With Pinterest, to operate the app through their API

With service providers who help us run the app (under confidentiality)

When required by law or to protect our rights

5. Data Retention

We keep your information only as long as necessary to operate the service.
If you disconnect your Pinterest account, we delete related data within a reasonable period.

6. Your Rights

You can revoke access to your Pinterest account anytime in your Pinterest settings.
You may also request that we delete any stored data by contacting us at contact@example.com
.

7. Security

We use reasonable security measures to protect your information, but no online service is 100% secure. Use the app at your own risk.
